title: Newsflash
body:
Brie never said she didn’t have a stunt double or that she did all her own stunts on her own without any stunt double involved at all.

She just said:

“I did my stunts.”

Like. You know they record the same scene multiple times, right? So even if they didn’t use the footage of Brie doing the stunts for whatever reason, that doesn’t mean she still DIDN’T do them. Or maybe her stunt double did the stunt first so as to test it was safe and see how it would look (like some of them do) and then Brie did it on camera for the final take?

Once again, taking a single thing Brie said and blowing it WAY out of context as an excuse to hate on her.

summary: I see so much hate directed at Brie Larson and I just don't get why. You don't find her funny. Ok. You don't like her. Ok. You...
body: I see so much hate directed at Brie Larson and I just don’t get why. You don’t find her funny. Ok. You don’t like her. Ok. You find her annoying. Ok I guess but there are actual videos on YouTube that are like “Compilation of EVERYONE OF THE ENDGAME CAST ABSOLUTELY LOATHING EVERY MINUTE THEY HAVE TO SPEND WITH BRIE LARSON” and then the comments are even worse and I just don’t get it. I have not seen one interview in which Brie was “cringey”, arrogant (at least not more than her co-stars and not in a not-humorous way) and I never felt like her interview partners hated her. Is misogyny really that hell of a drug?

body:
Superhero movies

The interview with Brie Larson and Jeremy Renner is a great example of the difference between the OG Avengers cast specifically and just her in particular. She talks about using the CM brand as a platform to push her agendas. And Jeremy is like I just love seeing the looks on the kids faces and what a difference it makes for them. And that he isn’t using the MCU to push anything other than happiness. Most of the cast don’t want to be around her because she only cares about the same thing everyone on Tumblr does and that’s taking something that is just supposed to be about good stories that teaches kids to be heroes. Taking that and making the only focus be gender/sexuality/race. Seems like people on here can’t see the world beyond these things and Brie is using all of you.
